nexpected events.\n\nWeaknesses:\n- A: show-off, not open to new ideas.\n- B: pretentious, wrong tone.\n- C: communication difficulty, egocentric, low education willingness.\n- D: hot temper, know-it-all, moody, loner.\n\nTeamwork/crew cooperation:\n- A: leadership but no explicit crew cooperation.\n- B: no explicit.\n- C: concern for others (positive), but egocentric and communication difficulty.\n- D: negative.\n\nGiven long-distance flights require crew cooperation, calm under pressure, decision-making, technical competence, reliability, and professional development.\n\nCandidate C has strong decision-making, calm, technical, attention, and explicit crew concern. Communication difficulty and egocentric are concerns but maybe mitigated by concern for others? Hard to say.\n\nCandidate B has strong stress handling, conscientiousness, weather assessment (critical), but lacks crew cooperation evidence.\n\nCandidate D has strong problem solving and responsibility, but poor crew traits.\n\nCandidate A has leadership and anticipation, but negative perception and not open to new ideas.\n\nThus I think Candidate C is still best due to explicit crew concern and decision-making. However the egocentric and communication issues could be severe. We could ask other agents if they have any additional positive teamwork info for B or D. But we already asked earlier and got none. Could ask if any agent has any other strengths for B beyond those listed, like teamwork. But likely none.\n\nThus I will provisionally prefer Candidate C, but note uncertainty due to communication and egocentric. I will state that.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON."}
